    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-08T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-08T19:00:00-05:00" n="34"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/953a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-08T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 8, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department desires immediate and specific information following points: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>What authorities now control Vladivostok?</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Do same authorities control Amur Province?</item>
                        <pb facs="0112" n="22" xml:id="pg_22"/>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>How are authorities constituted?</item>
                        <label>(4)</label>
                        <item>What is their attitude towards Bolshevik authorities Petrograd?</item>
                        <label>(5)</label>
                        <item>Are they supported unanimously by soldiers and sailors?</item>
                        <label>(6)</label>
                        <item>Is port open; is it likely to remain so?</item>
                        <label>(7)</label>
                        <item>What is attitude of authorities, of soldiers, and of sailors toward
                            foreign population?</item>
                        <label>(8)</label>
                        <item>How many troops at Vladivostok and how many sailors? Ditto in
                            Province?</item>
                        <label>(9)</label>
                        <item>What prospect <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> party
                            landing safely Vladivostok?</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>No answer telegram December 28, 5 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d34fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1918Russiav03#pg_214">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>,
                            p. 214</ref>.</note> Department desires full information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
